India, the worldâ€™s fourth-largest
polluter, connected renewable power plants with more than 2,700
megawatts of total capacity to the electricity grid this year,
the Ministry of New and Renewable Energy said in an e-mailed
statement.  That included 2,000 megawatts of wind capacity, 400
